  <h2>How to Choose the Right ATS Checker</h2>

  <p>The best ATS checker depends on what you need. If you want a quick, private score with the ability to auto-fix your resume, <a href="https://atsresumechecker.io">Resume Weapon</a> is the most practical choice — it's free, requires no signup, and includes AI rewriting.</p>

  <p>If you want extremely detailed keyword analysis and don't mind paying $50/month, Jobscan provides the most granular breakdown. If you're optimizing your LinkedIn profile alongside your resume, Resume Worded covers both.</p>

  <p>The key thing that matters most: whichever tool you use, always check your resume against the specific job posting you're applying to. Generic format scores are useful, but job-specific keyword matching is what actually determines whether you pass the ATS filter.</p>

  <h2>What Makes a Good ATS Resume Checker?</h2>

  <p><strong>Job-specific keyword matching.</strong> The best checkers compare your resume against a specific job posting, not just generic criteria. Real ATS systems evaluate keyword match rates against the job description, so your checker should too.</p>

  <p><strong>Formatting analysis.</strong> Beyond keywords, good checkers identify structural problems: tables that break parsing, creative headers the ATS can't recognize, multi-column layouts that jumble text, and file format issues.</p>

  <p><strong>Actionable feedback.</strong> A score alone isn't helpful. The checker should tell you exactly which keywords are missing, which formatting issues exist, and what to change. Ideally, it should show your matched keywords alongside the missing ones so you can prioritize.</p>

  <p><strong>Privacy.</strong> Your resume contains personal information — name, phone, address, work history. Tools that process your resume client-side (in your browser) are more private than those that upload it to their servers. Check the tool's privacy policy before uploading.</p>

  <p><strong>No forced signup.</strong> If a tool requires your email before showing results, it's often more interested in marketing to you than helping you. The best free tools let you check your score instantly without creating an account.</p>

